This paper deals with random matrices and their eigenvalues, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of noncrossing partition theory suggests a connection to combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DS), while the focus on convergence of empirical distributions may also relate to statistics (cs.ST) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
